ArgoCD Integration with Jenkins
We integrate ArgoCD with Jenkins using the GitOps approach so Jenkins updates the Kubernetes manifests in a GitHub repository, and ArgoCD automatically deploys the changes to the Kubernetes cluster.
1. Install ArgoCD
  - Install ArgoCD in the Kubernetes (EKS) cluster.
  - Verify that all ArgoCD pods are running.
2. Access ArgoCD
  - Expose the ArgoCD Server (LoadBalancer/Ingress/Port Forward).
  - Log in using the ArgoCD Admin credentials.
3. Connect ArgoCD to GitHub
  - ArgoCD → Settings → Repositories
  - Add the GitHub Manifest Repository.
  - Configure GitHub credentials (PAT or SSH Key).
4. Create an ArgoCD Application
  - ArgoCD → New Application
  - Enter:
    - Application Name
    - GitHub Manifest Repository URL
    - Repository Path
    - Target Revision (main)
    - Destination Cluster
    - Namespace
5. Configure Sync Policy
  - Enable:
    - Automatic Sync
    - Self Heal
    - Prune (Optional)
6. Configure Jenkins Pipeline
  - Build and push the Docker image to AWS ECR.
  - Update the image tag in the Kubernetes manifest repository.
  - Commit and push the manifest changes to GitHub.
7. Automatic Deployment
  - ArgoCD detects changes in the GitHub Manifest Repository.
  - ArgoCD synchronizes the updated manifests.
  - The application is automatically deployed to the Kubernetes (EKS) cluster.
8. Verify Deployment
  - Open the ArgoCD Dashboard.
  - Verify the application status is Healthy and Synced.
  - Verify the deployment:
    kubectl get pods -n <namespace>
    kubectl get svc -n <namespace>
